                    <note type="abstract" xml:lang="en" corresp="http://syriaca.org/persons http://syriaca.org/johnofephesus/persons">
                        <quote source="#bib1463-7">Sergius was a close collaborator of the miaphysite bishop Jacob Burd'oyo. He resided in Constantinople for a large part of his life and was eventually ordained miaphysite bishop of Antioch. However, it seems that he remained in Constantinople where he died around 560. During the last years of his life, he became an adherent of the tritheist doctrine.</quote>
                    </note>
                    <note xml:lang="en" type="abstract" xml:id="abstract-en-1463">In hagiography: Sergius of <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/1889">Tella</placeName> was the successor of <persName ref="//syriaca.org/person/69">Jacob Baradaeus</persName>. He accompanied his teacher
            to <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/586">Constantinople</placeName> where he was
          received by <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/779">the Empress
          Theodora</persName>.</note>
